"Of course, this is for the mother who was murdered by an [ICE agent](https://www.foxnews.com/category/us/immigration), and it's really sad. I know people are out marching and all today, and we need to speak up," [Sykes told Variety](https://x.com/variety/status/2010488950238904576?s=46) on the red carpet prior to the show. "We need to be out there and shut this rogue government down, because it's just awful what they're doing to people."

Good was shot and killed during an encounter with an ICE officer last week. Since then, protests have erupted in Minneapolis and across the U.S. Local officials, including Minneapolis Mayor Jacob Frey, have criticized the ICE officer's actions.

